                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote xml:id="d1" type="miniature">
                                <locus target="#51v #103v #103v #161v #178v #216r #216v"/>
                                <desc>The manuscript contains several miniatures, apparently of a later date than the main production unit. The catalogue 
                                description does not state which miniatures have been drawn on which pages. The miniatures have the 
                                following content:
                                a <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1044Prophet">Prophet Portrait</ref> of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1269Abraham">ʾAbrǝhāmAbraham</persName>;
                                    a <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8491Samuel">Sāmuʾel of Wāldǝbbā</persName> and his lion;
                                    a <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10581Zamika">Zamikāʾel ʾAragāwi</persName>;
                                    a <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Hāymānot</persName>;
                                    a <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3934Ewostate">ʾEwosṭātewos</persName>;
                                    a scene with the caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">ደብረ፡ ምጥማቅ፡</foreign> written above, and written below
                                    <foreign xml:lang="am">ወይዘሮ፡ ወለተ፡ <gap reason="lost"/></foreign>;
                                    the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1030Trinity">The Trinity</ref>;
                                    the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1068AdamandEveeatfruit">temptation of Adam and Eve</ref>;
                                    probably an <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref> of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3126Claudius">Claudius</persName> and
                                    <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2548Basilide">Basilides</persName>;
                                    a <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8974Stephen">St Stephen the Protomartyr</persName>;
                                    the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1036MercyCovenant">Covenant of Mercy</ref>;
                                    an <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7840Phanuel">Phanuel</persName>;
                                    an <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8083Raphael">Raphael</persName> conquering the
                                    <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11330Devil">Devil</persName>;
                                    a <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4306GabraMa">Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</persName>.
                                </desc>
                            </decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        
                        <additions>
                            <list>
                                <item xml:id="a1" corresp="#h2">
                                        <locus from="209r"/>
                                    <desc type="GuestText"><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2894RepCh175">Malkǝʾa Qʷǝsqʷām</title></desc>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez"><seg part="I">ሰላም፡ ለዝክረ፡ ስምኪ፡ በመጽሐፈ፡ ሕይወት፡ ልኩዕ። ወለሥዕርተ፡ ርእስኪ፡ ጸሊም፡ ከመ፡ ሕብረ፡ ቋዕ።</seg></q>
                                 </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="a2">
                                    <locus target="#1r"/>
                                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">The note states that the manuscript
                                        belongs to the church of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</placeName>.</desc>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez">ዳዊት፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">መድኃኔ፡ ዓለም።</placeName></q>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e1">
                                    <desc>The name of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13071Estifanos">ʿƎsṭifānos</persName> has been substituted by that of 
                                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13075Iyasu">ʾIyāsu</persName> in <ref target="#a1"/>.</desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e2">
                                    <locus target="#96v"/>
                                    <desc>The names of several persons originally mentioned in the manuscript, possibly owners, 
                                        have been erased. Among these were <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13072AsmaG">ʾAṣma Giyorgis</persName>, a name ending with 
                                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ክርስቶስ፡</foreign>, and other illegible names, on <locus target="#96v"/> and 
                                    repeated every few pages.</desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e3">
                                    <locus target="#187v"/>
                                    <desc>The name of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13073Zamikael">ZamikāʾelMikāʾel</persName> is mentioned.</desc>
                                </item>
                                
                                <item xml:id="e4">
                                    <desc>The catalogue description speculates whether the depiction of Dabra Mǝṭmāq in
                                        <ref target="#d1"/> with the mention of 
                                        a woman, whose name began with <foreign xml:lang="gez">Walatta</foreign>, depicts the presentation
                                        of this manuscript to the convent, possibly <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2327DabraM">Dabra Mǝṭmāq</placeName>.</desc>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                            
                        </additions>
                        
